    <section id="planets">
      <h2> <b> 🌍 Planets of our Solar System </b></h2>
      <article>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mercury:</strong> Closest planet to the Sun with extremely high temperatures.</li><br>
          <li><strong>Venus:</strong> Thick carbon dioxide atmosphere makes it the hottest planet.</li><br>
          <li><strong>Earth:</strong> The only planet known to support life and has liquid water on its surface.</li><br>
          <li><strong>Mars:</strong> It is red because of iron-rich dust.</li><br>
          <li><strong>Jupiter:</strong> Largest planet with a giant storm called the Great Red Spot.</li><br>
          <li><strong>Saturn:</strong> Has beautiful rings made of ice and rock.</li><br>
          <li><strong>Uranus:</strong> Rotates on its side with a tilt over 90°.</li><br>
          <li><strong>Neptune:</strong> Strongest winds in the Solar System.</li><br>
        </ul>
